<br>
In particular the suggestion to give us a debuff line seems very bad to me. The strength of the wizard class is that we are focused. Take that away and I guarantee you we will suffer.<br>
<br>
We lack hitpoints, armor, debuffs, heals, etc etc etc because that's what the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  other classes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are for. If we needed them any less to do the things they do, then we could not justify wanting to be (and being, imho) the biggest guns on the block by such a deleriously gratifying margin.<br>
<br>
But here we go, point by point<br>
1) more harvests...<br>
I have advocated this before, but in retrospect decided against it. Sure, it would be in line with the wizard class to specialize by sacrificing more spell slots for more damage... but harvest in its current form adds mainly to long term dps, not burndown dps.<br>
<br>
Now, if you tailored a harvest for burndown situations, that would be cool. Say... 3 hour refresh 1000 mana, instant cast... more or less useless for grinding, awesome for burning down a boss mob. That would be kinda spiffy...<br>
But I think something like this already exists as a group spell for enchanters (an ancient spell). That's even better; like I say, the more we depend on other classes, the more kickass nukes we can get while remaining balanced.<br>
<br>
