I would give the level 60 rain a good solid 3-4k damage potential over 4 - 6 waves. Tears of prexus has a base ratio of 4.73:1, so I would expect the 60 rain to break 5:1. Probably 5.25:1. The ancient version could hit a nice solid 6:1 (keep in mind our ancient nuke does 4.8:1, so 6:1 on an ancient rain seems conservative if anything) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/17/02 4:40:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=659.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: some other thoughts</span><hr size=1> I personaly dont think wizards needs alot of totaly new things. Letting harvest uppgrade so its somewhat similar amount of total mana at 60 as when you get it would be nice I think. Group spell shield at 60 would be nice too. But the only thing realy left to do since test changes and focus items, are damage uppgrade. Considering the cleric nuke, I would guess general caster upgrade will be around 25%, then add focus items to that. Should be enuff to make things interesting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucynlas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cynlas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/26/02 8:14:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=659.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: some other thoughts</span><hr size=1> Having just read a similar idea in a different thread that made me perk up, I thought I would pass it along.  Wizards are masters of direct damage and travel.  It seems that other classes that have specialties, i.e. poison and diseased based dots, or heavy magic based debuffs and such also have increased resistances to them.  I can only imagine that this would come from spending time experimenting in order to master the skills.<br>
<br>
My suggestions are rather simple.  We, wizards already have resistance spells that are self only.  But as I have experienced they do not stack with other such buffs.  I honestly don't see the reasoning.  We play with fire and ice and lightning as professionals, but our own defences do not work along with others.  They should stack, and I think that magic resistance should be added to one of our spells.<br>
<br>
My second suggestion is that we are also supposed to be the masters of travel.  If we can fold time and space into a neat little pocket only to open it up and be somewhere else, I would like to think that we would likewise be more resistant to being forced into another area.  A buff, and I think group buff would be not out of reason, simply because we already transport groups all over the realms, that would grant either immunity or higher resists to being summoned seems to me to be in-line with the class.  If the spell idea is too powerful then maybe a class level alternate experience skill.<br>
<br>
